                            <comment id="56953" author="adilger" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2013 17:31:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is an interop issue that is fixed with the patch to make the test more flexible.  That will work in the future, but since we aren&apos;t making new 2.3 releases it won&apos;t help for interop tests.  This problem will disappear once we have the final 2.4 release, since new master interop tests will use 2.4.x as the &quot;old&quot; version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56899" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2013 01:34:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been fixed on master by the patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4106&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4106&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So if need, we can back port the patch to b2_3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
